# Aeviti Design System — Cursor Rules

## Brand Identity
Aeviti is a biotech/diagnostics wellness platform blending clinical precision with human warmth.
Tagline: "Steady Health Intelligence"
Product: Aeviti Baseline — comprehensive biomarker interpretation

## Design Principles
1. **Single Typeface** — GT Walsheim throughout, hierarchy via weight + size contrast
2. **Light & Dark Duality** — Alternate warm ivory/cream sections with deep petrol sections
3. **Restrained Color** — Lead with neutrals, reserve deep green (terra) for CTAs only
4. **Generous Breathing Room** — 96–128px section padding
5. **Data as Story** — Present diagnostics with humanity, warm colors, contextual explanations

## Color System (from tailwind.config.ts)
- **Primary**: petrol (#1B3A4B) — clinical authority
- **Secondary**: sand (#C9A87C) — human warmth, ambient textures, bar charts
- **Accent**: terra (#00774D) — deep green, CTAs, buttons, overlines, step numbers
- **Neutrals**: ivory (#FAF7F2), cream (#F0EBE3), stone (#D4CEC4), warm-gray (#666666), charcoal (#111111), rich-black (#000000)
- **Text philosophy**: Clean black/white text for high contrast. On dark backgrounds, body text uses white at 60% opacity minimum. Green CTAs, petrol/sand for brand atmosphere
- **Semantic**: sage (#7A9E8E) for success/health, sky (#89B4C8) for info, alert (#C75D45) for warnings

## Typography Patterns
- **Typeface**: GT Walsheim is the sole typeface (self-hosted via @font-face in globals.css)
- **Display headings**: `font-display text-display-lg` — GT Walsheim Medium (500) or Bold (700), large sizes
- **Body text**: `font-body text-body-sm text-warm-gray` — GT Walsheim Regular (400) or Medium (500)
- **Data values**: `font-body text-body-sm font-medium tabular-nums` — GT Walsheim Medium at smaller sizes with tabular-nums for number alignment
- **Overlines**: `font-body text-overline font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em]` in terra or sand
- **Accent pattern**: Color + weight, not italic. `<span className="text-terra font-medium">accented word</span>` on light bg, `<span className="text-terra-light font-medium">accented word</span>` on dark bg
- **Typographic hierarchy**: Relies on weight contrast and size contrast rather than serif/sans contrast

## Component Architecture
- `/src/components/ui/` — Atomic components (FadeIn, Button, Typography, EmailCapture)
- `/src/components/sections/` — Page sections (Hero, Baseline, Coverage, etc.)
- `/src/components/visuals/` — Rich visual panel illustrations (charts, scheduling, protocol items)
- `/src/lib/tokens.ts` — Single source of truth for colors, categories, nav/footer data
- `/src/lib/hooks.ts` — useInView (scroll animations), useScrolled (nav)

## Section Pattern
Light sections: bg-ivory or bg-cream
Dark sections: gradient from petrol-dark to petrol, with grain-overlay and ambient-orb effects
Every section wraps content in max-w-[1100px] mx-auto

## When Adding New Sections
1. Create component in `/src/components/sections/`
2. Export from index.ts barrel
3. Add to page.tsx in desired position
4. Use FadeIn wrapper for scroll animations
5. Follow light/dark alternation pattern

## Card Pattern
- Background: bg-cream (light) or bg-white/[0.04] (dark)
- Border: border border-stone/[0.12] (light) or border-white/[0.06] (dark)
- Radius: rounded-card (14px)
- Padding: p-8
- Include visual illustration component when possible

## CTA Pattern
- Primary CTA: bg-terra text-white rounded-full
- Always "Join waitlist" with arrow → for this phase
- Email capture: pill-shaped input + button combo

## Status
Currently: waitlist/pre-launch phase
Primary CTA: waitlist signup
